Floyd Mayweather says sometimes he has to turn down request from fans in order to focus on himself and his daughters.

Mayweather took time out of his busy training schedule for his upcoming fight with Manny Pacquiao to take a trip to the 550ft ferris wheel at the LINQ hotel in Las Vegas.

And in a video posted on his Facebook page, the undefeated welterweight champion said that while it breaks his heart to say no to his fans for requests for autographs and photos, sometimes it is necessary.

